>         # PATCHED (report-mcp local fix): NEVER update current_source_name
>         # inside the loop. The original code did
>         #   current_source_name = step.output_filename or _default_output_filename(...)
>         # but `step.output_filename` already contains "X_edited.hwpx" from
>         # inside _apply_*_edits_to_source, and feeding that back as the next
>         # iteration's source_name made the internal writer add yet another
>         # "_edited" — eventually overflowing Windows MAX_PATH after ~30
>         # edits with a path like "X_edited_edited_..._edited.hwpx".
>         # Keeping source_name stable across the loop is safe: it is only used
>         # to name internal temp files; the final result.output_filename is
>         # recomputed below from resolved.source_name.
